 {"id":"jeffreysprompts.com-ctt5","title":"Implement CLI configuration file management","description":"## Task
Implement CLI configuration file support for JeffreysPrompts CLI.

## Scope
CLI client-side behavior; belongs in the public repo.
Depends on Premium CLI auth and sync flows for endpoint defaults.

## Features
- Create ~/.jeffreysprompts/config.json on first run
- Store API endpoint, auth tokens, preferences
- Support project-local .jeffreysprompts.json
- Environment variable overrides
- Config validation on load

## Configuration Options
```json
{
  "apiEndpoint": "https://api.jeffreysprompts.com",
  "defaultVisibility": "private",
  "syncOnSave": true,
  "offlineMode": false,
  "theme": "auto",
  "editor": "code",
  "outputFormat": "pretty"
}
```

## CLI Commands
- jfp config list - Show current config
- jfp config get <key> - Get config value
- jfp config set <key> <value> - Set config value
- jfp config reset - Reset to defaults
- jfp config path - Show config file location

## Logging Requirements
- Log config resolution order (project -> user -> env -> defaults)
- Log validation failures with actionable hints
- Log config migration steps when schema changes

## Success Criteria
- Config persists across sessions
- Project config overrides global
- Env vars take precedence
- Invalid config handled gracefully

